response.overview: Arctic Monkeys are an English rock band formed in Sheffield in 2002. The band consists of Alex Turner (lead vocals, guitar, piano), Jamie Cook (guitar, keyboards), Nick O'Malley (bass guitar, backing vocals), and Matt Helders (drums, vocals). Arctic Monkeys have released six studio albums and won seven Brit Awards. They became a hallmark in the indie rock genre and are known for their energetic performances and innovative music style, drawing influences from a wide range of genres.
